div.p:
Authors: Sariel Har-Peled, Sepideh Mahabadi
Download: PDF
Abstract: $
ewcommand{ all}{\mathbb{B}}
ewcommand{\dsQ}{{\mathcal{Q}}}
ewcommand{\dsS}{{\mathcal{S}}}$In this work we study a fair variant of the near neighbor problem. Namely, given a set of $n$ points $P$ and a parameter $r$, the goal is to preprocess the points, such that given a query point $q$, any point in the $r$-neighborhood of the query, i.e., $ all(q,r)$, have the same probability of being reported as the near neighbor.
